Moore: Zabra sɩngre wakate b kẽena yi mogrã zugu, la wã radar rãmba yelle sẽn n sɩnga la wẽed sõma yɩɩd pĩnda zabr batayo rãmb sẽn n lisd koomẽ ra togde tu kooma tẽngre na yil tɩ neb la yã b ye. English: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen. Moore: Tãnga bok zãaga zãng ne duniwã sẽn ketã, a be tãnga ye zug sẽn be Mak win ditgo. English: The submarines were not able to see the ships, so they had to go underwater. Moore: Tãnga bok zãaga zãng ne duniwã sẽn ketã, a be tãnga ye zug sẽn be Mak win ditgo.
